Einstein Case Classification and Einstein Case Wrap-Up help you remove the guesswork from completing case fields and resolve cases quickly and consistently.

Available in: Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

One-Minute Feature Tour: Einstein Case Classification and Case Routing

When you enable Einstein classification apps—Einstein Case Classification (1) and Einstein Case Wrap-Up (2)—your agents can see Einstein’s predictions at both ends of the case lifecycle. To get started, explore the Try Einstein version of the classification apps.

Einstein Classification Key Concepts:

* Models
* Segments
* Examples cases
* Case automation
* Case routing

Prepare for Einstein Classification Apps:
Review data requirements, address data problems early, and learn how to introduce these features to your support team.

Set Up Einstein Classification Apps:
Choose closed cases for Einstein to analyze, build classification models, and give agents access to predictions.

Use Einstein Classification Apps in the Service Console:
Einstein Case Classification and Einstein Case Wrap-Up help you fill in fields on cases by recommending or selecting field values based on similar closed cases.

Track Einstein Classification App Performance:
The performance dashboard shows you how well Einstein’s predictions are working. View the performance of predictions compared to the field value at the time the case is closed.

Update Your Einstein Classification Model:
Update an active Einstein classification model to add or remove fields, change which cases it applies to, or adjust field prediction settings.

Einstein Case Classification and Einstein Case Wrap-Up automate field completion and optionally route cases.
title: Autofill Case Fields with Einstein Classification Apps
